<small><strong>* Special Protocol for requesting an eagle for Eagle Scout Court of Honor:</strong></small>

Thank you for your interest in Liberty Wildlife and our educational ambassador eagles. As you can imagine we have many requests for these eagles to appear at Eagle Scout Courts of Honor. Unfortunately we are not able to meet all of these requests. Below see a list of requirements that help us determine which of the requests we are able to fill. Please evaluate these stipulations with your particular situation in mind and continue with the request if your particular program meets the requirements.
<ul>
 	<li>Your Eagle Scout project was done at Liberty Wildlife</li>
</ul>
Or
<ul>
 	<li>The program is for at least 2 Eagle Scouts</li>
 	<li>There is an opportunity for an educational element during the event</li>
 	<li>The program is not late in the evening (should end before 8:00)</li>
 	<li>Request needs to be made 4 weeks in advance</li>
 	<li>You are willing to make a donation of $500 to cover expenses</li>
 	<li>Mileage reimbursement for travel outside of Phoenix Metropolitan area</li>
 	<li>No out-of-town requests on week days</li>
</ul>
[/av_textblock]

