[/av_notification]

[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\']
OK, I\'ve been saying there is a new format for the blog coming for two weeks now, and here we are, the same old format, same old set up.  I wasn\'t pulling your leg, it really is going to change, but I found out the new blog can\'t go live until the rest of the web site is also up and running. So please be patient, one of these Mondays you\'ll see a new style and I think you\'ll like it!
In the meantime, let\'s take a look at the various happenings from the last 14 days of NUMEROUS intakes, tours of the facility, a killdeer family, and a lot of orphan great horned owls...
[/av_textblock]

[av_slideshow size=\'no scaling\' animation=\'slide\' autoplay=\'false\' interval=\'5\' control_layout=\'av-control-default\']
[av_slide slide_type=\'image\' id=\'728\' video=\'http://\' mobile_image=\'\' video_ratio=\'16:9\' title=\'\' link_apply=\'\' link=\'lightbox\' link_target=\'\' video_controls=\'\' video_mute=\'\' video_loop=\'\' video_autoplay=\'\']
Cayden the giver
[/av_slide]
[av_slide id=\'741\'][/av_slide]
[/av_slideshow]

[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\']
A lady brought Cayden, her seven year old son, to the window last week. It seems Cayden had a birthday party with some of his classmates and friends who were encouraged to visit our website wish list and choose gifts for Liberty in lieu of gifts for him. They had several armloads of thing we needed that the thoughtful kids had brought in to the party. We are grateful for the gifts, and very thankful that there are young people like this in the world who think of others before themselves. There is HOPE for the world after all! THANK YOU, Cayden!
[/av_textblock]

[av_slideshow size=\'no scaling\' animation=\'slide\' autoplay=\'false\' interval=\'5\' control_layout=\'av-control-default\']
[av_slide slide_type=\'image\' id=\'727\' video=\'http://\' mobile_image=\'\' video_ratio=\'16:9\' title=\'\' link_apply=\'\' link=\'lightbox\' link_target=\'\'][/av_slide]
[av_slide id=\'726\'][/av_slide]
[av_slide id=\'725\'][/av_slide]
[/av_slideshow]

[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\']
Insert text here!
[/av_textblock]

[av_slideshow size=\'no scaling\' animation=\'slide\' autoplay=\'false\' interval=\'5\' control_layout=\'av-control-default\']
[av_slide slide_type=\'image\' id=\'531\' video=\'http://\' mobile_image=\'\' video_ratio=\'16:9\' title=\'\' link_apply=\'\' link=\'lightbox\' link_target=\'\']
People even come out in the rain
[/av_slide]
[av_slide slide_type=\'image\' id=\'532\' video=\'\' mobile_image=\'\' video_ratio=\'\' title=\'\' link_apply=\'\' link=\'lightbox\' link_target=\'\']
Marko carries on inside
[/av_slide]
[/av_slideshow]

[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\']
Our public access program seems to be working as even in the rain and cold last weekend, people came out to visit the facility. Between rain events, the folks were able to walk around and tour the enclosures on the Education side, but in deference to any continued precipitation, the wildlife presentations were moved into the big classroom.
[/av_textblock]

[av_slideshow size=\'no scaling\' animation=\'slide\' autoplay=\'false\' interval=\'5\' control_layout=\'av-control-default\']
[av_slide slide_type=\'image\' id=\'526\' video=\'http://\' mobile_image=\'\' video_ratio=\'16:9\' title=\'\' link_apply=\'\' link=\'lightbox\' link_target=\'\']
The old office(s)
[/av_slide]
[av_slide slide_type=\'image\' id=\'527\' video=\'http://\' mobile_image=\'\' video_ratio=\'16:9\' title=\'\' link_apply=\'\' link=\'lightbox\' link_target=\'\']
The old ICU
[/av_slide]
[/av_slideshow]

[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\']
Just a couple of shots of what the old facility looks like as we approach the final “Last person out” stage of our presence at 11825 N 70th in Scottsdale. It’s amazing how much stuff you accumulate in 36 years, and the memories of all that happened and all we did still hang like echos in the wind. What we used to accomplish in these two rooms is now done in separate rooms dedicated to the tasks. Progress is rarely easy, and never cheap!
[/av_textblock]

[av_slideshow size=\'no scaling\' animation=\'slide\' autoplay=\'false\' interval=\'5\' control_layout=\'av-control-default\']
[av_slide slide_type=\'image\' id=\'528\' video=\'http://\' mobile_image=\'\' video_ratio=\'16:9\' title=\'\' link_apply=\'\' link=\'lightbox\' link_target=\'\']
The old Ed trailer moves to the new facility
[/av_slide]
[av_slide slide_type=\'image\' id=\'529\' video=\'http://\' mobile_image=\'\' video_ratio=\'16:9\' title=\'\' link_apply=\'\' link=\'lightbox\' link_target=\'\']
Tim finally gets the “Ed Trailer” on the road
[/av_slide]
[/av_slideshow]

[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\']
One of the major accomplishments in the process of vacating our old facility was moving the old”Education Trailer” that sat alongside the walkway inside the front gate. We are going to use this as weather-proof storage for various materials at the new facility. Moving it was no small task and took Herculean effort and great perseverance on the part of Tim who kept doggedly gnawing on the governmental red-tape and mechanical logistics that seemed to thwart every attempt to resurrect it. It had not been mobile in over two decades and was more-or-less a permanent adjunct to the old facility.
[/av_textblock]

